               <p>JOHN BURGESS. I am shopman to Mr. Cleobury, who is a <rs id="t18170702-12-viclabel66" type="occupation">clothier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-12-victim147 t18170702-12-viclabel66"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18170702-12-crimeloc67">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-12-crimeloc67" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-12-crimeloc67" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-12-off64 t18170702-12-crimeloc67"></join>. On the 24th of May, about half-past eight o'clock in the morning. I saw the prisoner take the trowsers from the door, and put them into his apron - He then ran across the road, and through Bow-churchyard; I pursued, calling out stop thief! he took them out of his apron and threw them away. I secured him behind a cart in Cloak-lane, and am sure he is the boy. He stood at the door three or four minutes. I lost sight of him, but soon found him again - He was running. I picked the trowsers up.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I know nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170702-12-verdict68" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18170702-12-verdict68" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14.</p>
